<section class="section" id="x2q-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading" id="x2q-in-brief-text">Xero to QuickBooks migration, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Switching from Xero to QuickBooks Online is a cross-platform migration with <strong>no Intuit-native one-click converter</strong> &mdash; the two systems structure data differently, so the work is to export from Xero, map to QuickBooks, rebuild what won&rsquo;t export, and verify. Your <strong>chart of accounts, contacts (customers and suppliers), open invoices, open bills, and manual journals</strong> carry over through Xero&rsquo;s exports. What does <strong>not</strong> come across cleanly is <strong>bank transactions and reconciliation history</strong> &mdash; Xero locks reconciled transactions to its own bank statement lines, and those don&rsquo;t translate, so they&rsquo;re handled with opening balances established at a chosen conversion date rather than re-imported line by line.</p>
      <p>The rest is rebuild and reconcile. Xero <strong>tracking categories</strong> map to QuickBooks <strong>classes or locations</strong>; <strong>repeating invoices</strong> and <strong>bank rules</strong> are recreated natively in QuickBooks, which handles them differently. Above all, the <strong>opening balances are tied back to Xero&rsquo;s trial balance</strong> at cutover &mdash; the verification step that makes the new file trustworthy. TechBrot Certified ProAdvisors run the full migration, document what transferred for your CPA, and fix the fee in writing after a free discovery call. Considering whether you should switch at all? See <a href="/quickbooks/compare/quickbooks-vs-xero/">QuickBooks vs Xero</a>. Migrating from a different platform? Start at <a href="/quickbooks/migration/other-software-to-qb/?intent=quickbooks-migration">other software to QuickBooks</a>. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc. or Xero.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

